y_k - 2\cos\theta y_{k-1} + y_{k-2} = 0.
\lambda^2 - 2\cos\theta \lambda + 1 = 0.
(\lambda - \cos\theta)(\lambda - \cos\theta) = 0
\cos^2\theta = 1
4(\cos^2\theta - 1)
y(k) - [2\cos(θ)]y(k-1) + y(k-2) = 0
 y(k)=\lambda^k 
  λ^2 - 2\cos(θ)λ + 1=0 
\Rightarrow \lambda_1 = \frac{2\cos(\theta)+\sqrt{4\cos(\theta)^2-4}}{2} \,, \lambda_2 = \frac{2\cos(\theta)-\sqrt{4\cos(\theta)^2-4}}{2} 
 \sqrt{4\cos(\theta)^2-4} = 2\sqrt{\cos^2(\theta)-1}=2 \sqrt{-1}\sqrt{1-\cos^2(\theta)}= 2 i\sin(\theta)\,.
 \lambda_1= \cos(\theta)+i\sin(\theta)\,,  \lambda_1= \cos(\theta)-i\sin(\theta)\,.
 y(k)=c_1{\lambda_1}^k + c_2 {\lambda_2}^k \,.  
